---
import { withBase } from '../../lib/url';
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import QuoteList from '../../components/QuoteList.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';

const t = TECHNIQUES.find((x) => x.slug === 'essential-dignities')!;
---

<Prose
  title={t.title}
  description={t.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Techniques', href: '/techniques/' }, { name: t.title }]}
  kicker="Technique"
  jsonLd={[{ '@type': 'Article', headline: t.title }]}
>
  <p>
    A figure is not equally strong everywhere. The houses themselves differ in strength (angles are
    strong, succedents middling, cadents weak), and each figure has houses where it stands well and
    houses where it stands ill. Essential dignity measures this strength of place, which shows how
    firmly a figure can act, apart from whether the figure itself is good or ill.
  </p>

  <h2>Weigh a figure's dignity</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Look the figure up in Cattan's reckoning of its good and ill houses. This is the course's main dignity tool, and it does not depend on any disputed attribution.</li>
    <li>Note the strength of its place: a figure in an angle is strong, in a succedent middling, in a cadent weak.</li>
    <li>Refine by triplicity when one element rules the chart: a figure stands stronger in a house of its own element. Use the course's default element grouping below.</li>
    <li>For exaltation or fall, name the system you are using, since Cattan's planetary table and the modern houses-as-signs table do not always agree.</li>
    <li>Read strength together with goodness, never as the same thing. An ill figure strongly placed acts with more force, not less.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>The course's default triplicities, taken from the figures' elements, are:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Element</th><th>Figures</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Fire</td><td>Fortuna Major, Rubeus, Puer, Amissio</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Air</td><td>Fortuna Minor, Puella, Laetitia, Conjunctio</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Water</td><td>Acquisitio, Cauda Draconis, Via, Populus</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Earth</td><td>Carcer, Tristitia, Albus, Caput Draconis</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>In the sources</h2>
  <QuoteList topic="dignities" noFigures />
  <p>
    Cattan's reckoning of each figure's good and ill houses is quoted on the
    <a href={withBase('/figures/')}>individual figure pages</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The complete Golden Dawn table (every figure's house, exaltation, triplicity, fall and
    detriment) is reproduced in the library:
    <a href={withBase('/library/crowley/dignities-and-aspects/')}>the Table of Essential Dignities</a>.
  </p>
</Prose>
